# Mobile Cursor → Railway deploy

Production deploys only from **`main`** (GitHub Actions → Railway + Cloudflare).

Cursor Mobile / cloud agents push to **`cursor/*` branches**. Those do **not** appear on Railway until they are on `main`.

## Happy path (automatic)

1. Push to `cursor/*` with **no PR** → CI **Ensure Cursor mobile PR** opens a draft PR, runs Maven verify, squash-merges to `main`, and dispatches Railway + Cloudflare (skip re-verify).
2. Push to `cursor/*` with a PR already open → PR Verify → **Ship Cursor mobile PR** (unless labeled `hold` / `no-ship`) → same deploy dispatch.
3. Do not rely on “open PR only” from a `GITHUB_TOKEN` bot — that does not re-trigger workflows; the ensure job ships orphans in-process.

## When the user wants mobile changes live and auto-ship stalled

1. `./scripts/ship-mobile-changes.sh` (list pending + PR links)
2. Prefer `./scripts/ship-mobile-changes.sh --ensure-pr` (opens draft PRs; CI ships after verify)
3. Fallback: `./scripts/ship-mobile-changes.sh --apply` (cherry-pick + push)
4. Optional: `./scripts/ship-mobile-changes.sh --prune` (delete remote `cursor/*` already on main)
5. Confirm Actions: ship → **Deploy to Railway** (and Cloudflare).
6. Do not tell the user changes are deployed while they only exist on a `cursor/*` branch or an open draft PR.

## When finishing cloud/mobile UI work yourself

- Prefer landing on **`main`** (push or merge), not `master`.
- On a `cursor/*` branch: push the branch; CI opens the PR if needed — do not stop at a branch-only push.
- After verify-worthy changes, get them onto `main` (merge/ship) so Railway updates.
- Bump asset / service-worker cache versions when shipping CSS/JS/static UI fixes so clients see the new build.
